\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9962819 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7622360\charrsid9248556 Yes they would. But - in the very old days people that was on the Parish - in the winter - they used to give the lads
 corduroy trousers and - and clogs. And - they used to go to different depots in Bootle - and they'd get a gig loaf and some tea and sugar and oatmeal. Yes. Very poor. And I think the bread used to be baked in - what workhouse - at Stanley - East End Hosp
ital now. Yes, that used to be the workhouse.
